1
00:00:00,000 --> 00:00:01,826
Before a medical appointment

2
00:00:01,826 --> 00:00:03,066
the hardest part is often

3
00:00:03,066 --> 00:00:04,746
not a single symptom

4
00:00:04,746 --> 00:00:05,600
It is remembering

5
00:00:05,600 --> 00:00:07,706
the full story clearly

6
00:00:07,706 --> 00:00:09,773
ClinDiary is a local-first

7
00:00:09,773 --> 00:00:10,826
mobile diary for

8
00:00:10,826 --> 00:00:12,426
daily health context

9
00:00:12,426 --> 00:00:14,346
It is not an AI doctor

10
00:00:14,346 --> 00:00:15,546
It is a private memory

11
00:00:15,546 --> 00:00:16,639
layer that helps users

12
00:00:16,639 --> 00:00:17,546
organize what

13
00:00:17,546 --> 00:00:19,252
happened between visits

14
00:00:19,252 --> 00:00:20,452
The user starts with

15
00:00:20,452 --> 00:00:21,852
a voice check-in

16
00:00:21,852 --> 00:00:23,252
They speak in English

17
00:00:23,252 --> 00:00:24,572
review the transcript

18
00:00:24,572 --> 00:00:26,252
and send it to Gemma

19
00:00:26,252 --> 00:00:28,052
Gemma drafts the check-in

20
00:00:28,052 --> 00:00:30,052
from what the user actually said

21
00:00:30,052 --> 00:00:31,552
sleep, mood, stress

22
00:00:31,552 --> 00:00:32,952
hydration and pain

23
00:00:32,952 --> 00:00:34,552
notes and daily signals

24
00:00:34,552 --> 00:00:36,052
If symptoms are mentioned

25
00:00:36,052 --> 00:00:37,852
Gemma can add symptom drafts

26
00:00:37,852 --> 00:00:39,972
with severity from zero to ten

27
00:00:39,972 --> 00:00:41,732
duration and body location

28
00:00:41,732 --> 00:00:43,332
The user stays in control

29
00:00:43,332 --> 00:00:45,252
unclear details can remain empty

30
00:00:45,252 --> 00:00:46,852
Gemma can ask questions

31
00:00:46,852 --> 00:00:48,452
and everything is reviewed

32
00:00:48,452 --> 00:00:49,452
before saving

33
00:00:49,452 --> 00:00:50,652
The goal is not

34
00:00:50,652 --> 00:00:52,172
to diagnose the symptom

35
00:00:52,172 --> 00:00:53,972
It is to preserve details

36
00:00:53,972 --> 00:00:55,172
usually forgotten

37
00:00:55,172 --> 00:00:56,052
Medication context

38
00:00:56,052 --> 00:00:57,532
can be tracked too

39
00:00:57,532 --> 00:00:58,732
including schedules

40
00:00:58,732 --> 00:01:00,852
adherence context and reminders

41
00:01:00,852 --> 00:01:03,212
but ClinDiary does not prescribe medications

42
00:01:03,212 --> 00:01:05,052
or suggest dosage changes

43
00:01:05,052 --> 00:01:06,452
Documents can be stored

44
00:01:06,452 --> 00:01:08,252
in an encrypted local vault

45
00:01:08,252 --> 00:01:09,252
on the device

46
00:01:09,252 --> 00:01:10,972
keeping important health context

47
00:01:10,972 --> 00:01:12,212
close to the user

48
00:01:12,212 --> 00:01:13,452
Ask Files searches

49
00:01:13,452 --> 00:01:15,092
local document context

50
00:01:15,092 --> 00:01:16,612
and shows cited snippets

51
00:01:16,612 --> 00:01:18,052
so answers stay grounded

52
00:01:18,052 --> 00:01:19,772
in what was actually saved

53
00:01:19,772 --> 00:01:21,372
When the model is available

54
00:01:21,372 --> 00:01:22,852
Gemma can help summarize

55
00:01:22,852 --> 00:01:24,252
and explain local context

56
00:01:24,252 --> 00:01:25,852
with cautious instructions

57
00:01:25,852 --> 00:01:27,452
and clear safety boundaries

58
00:01:27,452 --> 00:01:29,652
The app exposes the active AI path

59
00:01:29,652 --> 00:01:31,332
including provider and runtime

60
00:01:31,332 --> 00:01:33,452
model status and cloud-use proof

61
00:01:33,452 --> 00:01:34,972
Daily, weekly, monthly

62
00:01:34,972 --> 00:01:36,452
and pre-visit recaps

63
00:01:36,452 --> 00:01:37,852
turn local entries into

64
00:01:37,852 --> 00:01:39,212
readable summaries

65
00:01:39,212 --> 00:01:40,652
users can review

66
00:01:40,652 --> 00:01:42,652
Safety logic stays conservative

67
00:01:42,652 --> 00:01:44,412
Prevention reminders are rule-based

68
00:01:44,412 --> 00:01:45,652
discussion prompts

69
00:01:45,652 --> 00:01:46,972
not AI decisions

70
00:01:46,972 --> 00:01:49,052
about diagnosis or emergencies

71
00:01:49,052 --> 00:01:50,252
The goal is simple

72
00:01:50,252 --> 00:01:51,452
less forgotten context

73
00:01:51,452 --> 00:01:53,172
more prepared conversations

74
00:01:53,172 --> 00:01:54,772
and privacy by default

75
00:01:54,772 --> 00:01:56,052
ClinDiary is a memory

76
00:01:56,052 --> 00:01:57,052
layer for health

77
00:01:57,052 --> 00:01:58,652
powered by local data and

78
00:01:58,652 --> 00:02:00,452
Gemma-assisted summaries
